Require tickets for entry. Evenings tend to be busy. The panoramic view encompasses sights like Bandarawela Central College, Bandarawela Town, Heeloya Railway Station, and the Mahamewna Buddhist Monastery. Accessible by vehicles, parking is … Read more
Require tickets for entry. Evenings tend to be busy. The panoramic view encompasses sights like Bandarawela Central College, Bandarawela Town, Heeloya Railway Station, and the Mahamewna Buddhist Monastery. Accessible by vehicles, parking is scarce, and the narrow road allows only one vehicle at a time. Consider parking at Mahaulpatha Temple, around a 500m walk away, for a more convenient visit

Porawagala stands as a viewing point elevated at 1,330 meters (4,360 ft), offering an overlook of Bandarawela town in Sri Lanka. Positioned approximately 3 km to the east of Bandarawela railway station and bus stand, it provides scenic views.”
Ticket Rs.100 per adult. Final part of the road is very narrow, only good thing is it is one way. Toilet facilities available. Parking space limited.

Place looks like it has built recently. Some constructions are still on going. It has a beautiful view of the town and the train track. We were lucky to spot a train. You have to buy a ticket to enter. It is worth the price because the place is well maintained. Parking is very limited and the road is very narrow. Be cautious if you are taking a big van or bus. I think they are building a vehicle park also.
